changeCallerFee(uint256).details: 10000 = No fee, 10100 = 1%, 10001 = 0.01%If caller fee is above 8.33% because then a second feefill would happen on annual subs

params._maxRemits: New number of max remits per transaction

constructor.details: 10000 = No fee, 10100 = 1%, 10001 = 0.01%If caller fee is above 8.33% because then a second feefill would happen on annual subs

params.allowSystemFee_: Is the system fee turned on?
params.callerFee_: The percentage of the subscription the Caller is paid each period
params.systemFee_: The amount of chain token in wei the system is paid

createSubscription(uint256,address,(stri.details: In weiToken amount must be above token minimum for ERC20 tokenToken address must be whitelisted by adminDetails are posted in event logs not storage0 = Weekly, 1 = Monthly, 2 = Quarterly, 3 = YearlyThe dueDay will be within differing ranges based on frequency.

params.amount: Amount of ERC20 tokens paid each cycle
params.dueDay: The day in the cycle the subscription is due

params.bySubscriber: If true then get subscriptions user is subscribed to. If false get subs user created

getSubByIndex(bytes32,uint8,uint16).details: 0 = Weekly, 1 = Monthly, 2 = Quarterly, 3 = YearlyThe dueDay will be within differing ranges based on frequency.

params.dueDay: The day in the cycle the subscription is due

remit().details: Transfers the oldest outstanding transactions that are past their due dateIf system fee is set then the chain token must also be added to the transactionEach call will transmit either the total amount of current transactions due or the maxRemits whichever is smallerThe function will paginate so multiple calls can be made per day to clear the queue

subscribe((bytes32,uint256,address,addre.details: Requires ERC20 allowance to be set before function is called
